programme.title: James Toney vs Mike McCallum 1

programme.title: James Toney vs Mike McCallum 2

programme.title: Roy Jones Jr vs Julio Ceasar Gonzalez

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Water Adventures
programme.desc: We are captivated by oceans, rivers, and lakes - the power, the flow, the reflective stillness. And as we seek to get closer, we immerse ourselves in an expanding range of aquatic experiences.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: NEW: The Siege of Malta
programme.desc: At last here is the definitive story of heroism and hardship of a people uniquely and collectively awarded the George Cross 'for gallantry', and told by some of the heroic survivors.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The battles of the first world war were battles of attrition and trenches; the battles of the second world war were vastly different. In this episode we study tank battles, blitzkrieg, commando raids, amphibious landings, and mobile warfare in the desert.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The second world war was conflict on an unprecedented scale. Its battles set new marks for the sheer size of forces deployed and for the power of their weapons. In this episode we study the first battle at sea, and the largest army to have ever marched.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A war that reached every continent and touched every sort of terrain demanded every sort of strategy. In this episode we examine battles fought at sea, and in the jungle, in city streets, invasions from the air, and retreats from the land.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Battles are almost always about territory. Advancing the front line, seizing the port, the city, the oil field. The fate of nations in the war rose and fell on battles that took territory. Singapore, Monte Casino, Stalingrad...all about territory.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Every war seized new tactics; some inspired, some desperate, all attempting to influence the course of battles. Campaigns waged against non military targets to demoralize. Suicide missions launched when traditional weapons failed. Rules were rewritten.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A world war is a patchwork of actions. Land. Sea. Air. Massive, or small scale. The stories of these actions, are just as varied. This episode describes battles of amphibious forces, climate, geography, and the problems of supply.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Through history, armies marched to face each other on favored ground and clashed to decide a campaign, a war, an empire. With the 20th century that changed. The battles of the WWII happened anywhere and everywhere, in every weather and climate.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Mafia Connection
programme.desc: Lucky Luciano, a mafia boss of the 1930s, was in jail in 1942 on charges of running prostitution rings. US intelligence services did a deal with him and he got the Italians to share intelligence on German U boat movements.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Hardy Amies and Operation Ratweek
programme.desc: Operation Ratweek’s existence has always been denied. However WMR has now discovered evidence that it existed and was carried out.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Special Interrogation Group
programme.desc: The SIG consisted of German speaking Jewish volunteers from Palestine. They had a highly dangerous job: which was to pose as Germans behind enemy lines and extract intelligence and do acts of sabotage. Few had a long-life expectancy.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: In this programme we bring the RAF story into the modern era. Another aircraft to have extended the RAF’s capabilities is the C130 Hercules. This aircraft has proved its capabilities in countless environments from resupply, to dropping paratroopers.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The RAF’s maritime role is often overlooked. Between the wars the RAF operated elegant flying boats to patrol the far flung corners of the Empire.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: After the war, RAF transports helped keep Berliners alive during the Soviet blockade of the city in 1948/49. As well as flying round-the-clock operations into the airport, Sunderland flying boats delivered supplies by landing on Lake Havel near the city.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: By the end of the First World War the RAF had bombers that could fly to Berlin and back. For the first time in a thousand years British civilians found themselves under direct attack - by Zeppelin airships and Gotha bombers.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: By the end of the war the RAF had aircraft that could escort bombers to targets deep inside Germany and back. With the Gloster Meteor, the RAF had also entered the ‘Jet Age’. Aircraft like the Hawker Hunter and F-86 Sabre took the RAF supersonic.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The 1920s and 30s were uncertain times for the RAF as well as all other armed services. With peace came cuts in spending on new aircraft development.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The series begins before WWI when military commanders struggled to understand what uses aviation might have. The Wright Brothers had been the first to fly a powered aircraft in controlled flight in 1903, but even by 1914 aircraft were still underpowered.
programme.sub-title: Useless for the Purposes of War

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The Means To Victory
programme.desc: The Means to Victory: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The World At War
programme.desc: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Terror of The World
programme.desc: Terror of the World: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Mass Graves
programme.desc: This first episode provides context for when, how and why the mobile death squads, or EZG, were established.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Judenfrei
programme.desc: In December 1941, after the EZG’s intervention, Romania, Bulgaria, Hungary and the Baltic states are declared 'Judenfrei': free of Jews.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Funeral Pyres
programme.desc: Faced with the advancing Soviet troops, Nazi Germany decided to have the bodies of the death camp victims dug up and burned in graves

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Time Of Reckoning
programme.desc: After being judged at the Nuremberg trials, the majority of those responsible for the murder of nearly 1.5 million Jews would walk free in the 1950s

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Rise of The Bomber
programme.desc: Rise of the Bomber: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Christmas She Wrote
programme.desc: When Kayleigh, a romance writer, has her column cancelled right before Christmas, she heads home to reconnect with her family. Kayleigh gets an unexpected visit from the man who cancelled her column.

programme.title: The Holiday Sitter
programme.desc: When Sam, a workaholic bachelor, babysits his niece and nephew before the holidays, he recruits help from their handsome neighbor Jason and finds himself in an unexpected romance.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Ellie is told by a fortune teller that she must resolve her past and make amends with all of those she ghosted before Christmas and discovers love in the process.

programme.title: Boyfriends of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Leading up to Christmas, marketing executive, Lauren, is visited by the ghosts of four ex boyfriends. She must learn to open her heart or risk losing her best friend, Nate.

programme.title: In Merry Measure
programme.desc: When pop star Darcy returns home to spend Christmas with her sister and niece, she unexpectedly finds herself coaching the high school choir with her onetime rival, Adam.

programme.title: Christmas Comes Twice
programme.desc: Cheryl is the top newscaster who has achieved her dreams but has regrets about the guy who got away five years earlier. When the Christmas carnival comes to town, a ride around the carousel takes her back in time...

programme.title: The Santa Stakeout
programme.desc: Tanya is a police detective who is reluctantly partnered with fellow detective Ryan to solve a recent string of heists taking place during high-profile holiday parties around town. They go undercover as newlyweds...

programme.title: A Dickens of a Holiday!
programme.desc: To make the 100th anniversary of her hometown’s Victorian festival a success, Cassie invites action movie star and former high school classmate Jake to play Scrooge in 'A Christmas Carol'.

programme.title: All Saints Christmas
programme.desc: Lisette is a popular R&B singer who’s getting ready to travel home to New Orleans for Christmas.

programme.title: Nantucket Noel
programme.desc: During the Seaside Noel celebrations Christina learns of a developer who is planning to tear down the wharf that is home to her toy store. Tensions rise as she falls for the developer's son, Andy.

programme.title: December Bride
programme.desc: The last person Layla O’Reilly wants as her date to the wedding between her ex-fiancé and her own cousin is Seth Murphy, the one who introduced the soon-to-be-married couple. But it’s better than showing up alone.

programme.title: Toward Intimacy
programme.desc: Toward Intimacy" celebrates the rights of women with disabilities to pursue intimate relationships. This one-hour film features personal stories from four Canadian women, addressing sexuality, self-esteem, stereotypes, and parenting.

programme.title: Hands Of History
programme.desc: In this acclaimed 1994 documentary, Loretta Todd, a leading figure in Indigenous cinema in Canada, profiles four contemporary female artists.The film is a moving testimony to the vital role Indigenous women play in nurturing Indigenous cultures.

programme.title: Cornet At Night
programme.desc: This film recalls rural life on the Prairies in the 1930s. A farmer's young son, sent to town to hire a man for the harvest, readily accepts when an itinerant trumpet player, down on his luck, begs a chance.

programme.title: Kevin Alec
programme.desc: In the mountainous country near Lillooet, eleven-year-old Kevin Alec of the Fountain Indian Reserve learns to make fishnets with his grandfather, and skin and tan hides with his aunt. Will he eventually abandon his traditional way of life?

programme.title: Kanehsatake 270 Years Of Resistance
programme.desc: In July 1990, a dispute over a proposed golf course to be built on Kanien'kéhaka (Mohawk) lands in Oka, Quebec, set the stage for an historic confrontation that would grab international headlines and sear itself into the Canadian consciousness.

programme.title: Chile Obstinate Memory
programme.desc: A generation of young Chileans has grown up with no knowledge of the facts surrounding the military coup of September 11, 1973. Now, Patricio Guzmán returns to Chile, after 23 years. The time has come to reveal the long-forgotten truth.

programme.title: Special Delivery
programme.desc: The first big mistake Ralph makes is not clearing the snow from the front walk, and his life goes downhill from that point on. By the end of the story, the mailman has fatally slipped on his job, and Alice, his wife, doesn't live there anymore.

programme.title: The Secret Order
programme.desc: Phil Comeau shines a spotlight on the Ordre de Jacques-Cartier and paints a gripping portrait of the social and political struggles of Canadian francophone-minority communities.

programme.title: Men of the Deeps
programme.desc: Men of the Deeps is a moving portrait of a group of former Cape Breton miners gathered together by their love of song. They are all members of the Men of the Deeps chorus, whose performances of traditional and contemporary songs evoke their working lives

programme.title: Notmans World
programme.desc: William Notman was a man of rare talent. Photography was still in its infancy when he opened his first studio--in Montréal--in the late 1850s. He rapidly turned his art, and a budding technology, into a highly successful business.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: Patricias Moving Picture
programme.desc: Patricia Garner approached middle age in despair. Sandwiched between changing social values and the loss of her own family role, she was afraid of the future. This film tells of her inspiring struggles and successes.

programme.title: Sunrise Over Tiananmen Square
programme.desc: Shui-Bo Wang's animated documentary intertwines personal journey with history, exploring China's '60s-'80s upheavals. From symbol of hope to tragedy, it depicts Wang's roles from Red Guard to teacher, exploring idealism and intolerance.

programme.title: Forgotten Warriors
programme.desc: Although they could not be conscripted, when World War II was declared, thousands of Indigenous Canadian men and women enlisted and fought alongside their non-Indigenous countrymen. They fought for freedom while being denied their own.

programme.title: Yul 871
programme.desc: A Paris engineer on Flight YUL 871 to Montréal seeks his displaced parents amid the restlessness of the era. Amidst a brief love affair and Expo visits, he finds connection with a little girl.

programme.title: Kathleen Shannon On Film Feminism Other Dreams
programme.desc: With intelligence and humour, documentary filmmaker, Kathleen Shannon speaks her formative years at the National Film Board, and the gradual awakening of an unshakeable determination to give women filmmakers a chance to tell their stories of the world

programme.title: Lay Down Your Heart
programme.desc: An accomplished artist, a lifelong performer and a person with Down syndrome, Niall McNeil has built a unique family tree of blood and chosen relations made up of his closest friends and collaborators.

programme.title: Mountain Of Sgaana
programme.desc: This film spins a magical tale of a young man who is stolen away to the spirit world, and the young woman who rescues him. Haida filmmaker Christopher Auchter’s dream-like gem brilliantly entwines traditional animation with formal elements of Haida art.

programme.title: Lipsett Diaries
programme.desc: Lipsett Diaries is a descent into the maelstrom of anguish that tormented famed Canadian experimental filmmaker Arthur Lipsett, who died prematurely at age 49.

programme.title: Under The Willow Tree Pioneer Chinese Women In Canada
programme.desc: Explore the untold history of Chinese Canadian women, from their courageous journeys to the challenges they faced in Canada. Through photos, recollections, and narration by Dora Nipp, this film captures their resilience and cultural legacy.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: After inheriting her grandmother’s The Merry & Bright Candy Cane Kitchen, Kate Bracwell hires company recovery specialist Gabe Sumner to help improve the company. But it’s not all plain sailing.

programme.title: Christmas on the Slopes
programme.desc: In a Christmas miracle, an American celebrity chef finds inspiration - and her perfect partner - in the heart of a mountain resort and in the arms of its handsome, hot-headed and passionate head-Chef.

programme.title: Snowbound for Christmas
programme.desc: Rachel, eager to impress her new boss Adrian, lands a spot on a big project. But before the presentation, a snowstorm traps Rachel and Adrian at a resort where they realize there is more to their relationship than just business.

programme.title: A Christmas Dance Reunion
programme.desc: When a New York lawyer returns home for the holidays, she ditches her city life to save her family’s Christmas vacation resort with the help of her childhood crush and an epic dance partner.

programme.title: The Christmas Sitters
programme.desc: A week before Christmas, Nora’s best friends’ travel plans go awry and she is asked to watch their two kids and dog. But Nora is surprised when the children’s Uncle Max shows up too, he has also been asked to watch them.

programme.title: Christmas Lucky Charm
programme.desc: Every boyfriend Jessica has had found the love of his life right after dating her. Just as Jessica swears off dating for the Christmas season, a handsome gallery owner moves in across the street.

programme.title: Forever Christmas
programme.desc: When workaholic Sophie starts working on a holiday-season show about Will, who celebrates Christmas every day of the year, she finds herself falling for her mysterious, unlikely new star, renewing her long-lost faith in Christmas in the process.

programme.title: A Gift For Christmas
programme.desc: One day when cycling to work, Darcy accidentally crashes into a stranger walking his dog. He is taken to a hospital, leaving his puppy and a mysterious Christmas gift behind. As Darcy helps Aidan battle amnesia, together they find out who he really is.

programme.title: The Picture of Christmas
programme.desc: Ember Morley, a graphic designer and aspiring storybook illustrator in Manhattan is surprised when she learns she has inherited her Grandmother’s Christmas tree farm.

programme.title: A Royal Christmas on Ice
programme.desc: Looking to escape his Royal life, a dashing prince comes to the United States to start a business in a small town in upstate New York and winds up falling for a former Olympic ice skater.

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Weihnachtswunderland
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtszeit in New York ist für die erfolglose Künstlerin Heidi Neill alles andere als wundervoll.

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Eine Hochzeit an Weihnachten
programme.desc: Haley Foster entkam ihrer Kleinstadt-Kindheit in Pineridge und baute sich ein Großstadtleben in Los Angeles als Top-Hochzeitsplanerin in einer elitären und mächtigen Firma auf, die von Frau Reynolds geleitet wird.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Mrs. Miracle – Ein Zauberhaftes Kindermädchen
programme.desc: Der überforderte Witwer Seth Webster hat alle Hände voll zu tun, seine beiden Zwillinge Judd und Jason unter Kontrolle zu halten.

programme.title: Alone for Christmas
programme.desc: Wenn eine Familie an Heiligabend das Haus von Oma besucht, lässt sie ihren Hund allein zu Hause. Und wenn Einbrecher versuchen, die Geschenke unter dem Baum hervorzuholen, um sie zu stoppen.

programme.title: Melrose Place: Weihnachtsgefühle
programme.desc: Alison muss sich von ihrer Operation erholen. Billy kümmert sich um sie, allerdings etwas überfürsorglich. Jake versucht derweil, Jo näher zu kommen, doch sie braucht noch Zeit, um nachzudenken.

programme.title: Weihnachtsmann gesucht
programme.desc: Weihnachten, das Fest der Liebe, steht vor der Tür. Für Johannes (Christoph Waltz), einen etwas verschrobenen Zoohändler, droht dieses jedoch zum schlimmsten seines Lebens zu werden.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Melrose Place: Beinahe wäre es fast passiert
programme.desc: Eve setzt ihre Bewährungsstrafe aufs Spiel und will sich nach Mexiko absetzen. Amanda verliert durch den Fenstersturz ihr Baby. Peter findet heraus, dass dem Labor bei Kyles Spermaprobe ein fataler Fehler unterlaufen ist.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtswunsch
programme.desc: Wenn Ethan und seine kleine Schwester Hallie wünschen sich kein Spielzeug zu Weihnachten. Sie wünschen sich ein Wunder: Dass ihre geschiedenen Eltern sich wieder verlieben.

programme.title: Wer an Wunder glaubt
programme.desc: Als junges Mädchen war Suzie (Hayden Panettiere, „Nashville\\") offenherzig, optimistisch und spielte auch gerne mal den ein oder anderen Streich. Aber als aus Suzie Susan wurde, verschwand ihre spielerische und einnehmende Persönlichkeit über die Jahre.

programme.title: Alone for Christmas
programme.desc: Wenn eine Familie an Heiligabend das Haus von Oma besucht, lässt sie ihren Hund allein zu Hause. Und wenn Einbrecher versuchen, die Geschenke unter dem Baum hervorzuholen, um sie zu stoppen.

programme.title: Simsalabim Sabrina: Weihnachtsstimmung
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten und Gems Selbstgefälligkeit macht alle verrückt. Sabrina will ihr die Augen öffnen. Sie inszeniert mit ihrer Familie eine Gespenster-Erscheinung wie in Charles Dickens' Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: PAA Christmas
programme.desc: People Are Awesome Christmas edition.

programme.title: Unsere Lehrerin die Weihnachtshexe
programme.desc: Während des Tages ist Paola eine gewöhnliche Grundschullehrerin, doch nachts verwandelt sie sich in die Weihnachtshexe, eine magische Wesenheit, die den braven Kindern Geschenke macht.

programme.title: Regal Academy: Die Falle der Schneekönigin
programme.desc: Um gegen die sechs großen Märchenfamilien anzukommen, lässt die Schneekönigin Hawks Schwester Fala frei, die sie vor Jahren entführt hat, und benutzt sie als Spielfigur innerhalb der Schule.

programme.title: Little Charmers: Santa Sparkle
programme.desc: Als Hazel die Funkelnacht für alle im Zauberstädtchen ruiniert, hoffen die Zaubersternchen, dass Santa Sparkles Magie alles in Ordnung bringt. Doch kommt wahre Funkelnacht-Magie nicht von innen?

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda: Geschenkte Zeit
programme.desc: Zum jährlichen Winterfestival, hat Po nicht genug Geld, um seinem Dad ein Geschenk zu kaufen. Daher nimmt er einen Job als Kopfgeldjäger an und muss einen gefährlichen, entlaufenen Sträfling einfangen. Doch Po’s Plan verläuft nicht wie erhofft.

programme.title: The Fairly Odd Parents: Fröhliche Wunschnachten!
programme.desc: Timmy bekommt nicht das zu Weihnachten, was er möchte. Also wünscht er es sich einfach. Seine Freunde können das nicht, darum wünscht sich Timmy für alle Kinder einen Zaubergutschein, mit dem sie sich einen Wunsch erfüllen können.

programme.title: SpongeBob Schwammkopf: Weihnachten unter Wasser
programme.desc: Sandy erzählt SpongeBob von Weihnachten und vom Weihnachtsmann. Sponge ist natürlich hellauf begeistert und erzählt in der ganzen Stadt davon. Nun schreiben alle brav ihre Wunschzettel und warten aufs Christkind, nein, den Weihnachtsmann.

programme.title: See Dad Run: Dad und das Weihnachtsgratin
programme.desc: Amy muss am Heiligabend arbeiten und ist darüber so traurig, dass die Familie beschließt, ihr eine ganz besondere Freude zu machen. Dazu müssen David und die Kinder sich allerdings durch einige vorweihnachtliche Hindernisse im Supermarkt kämpfen.

programme.title: Invader Zim: Das schrecklichste Weihnachtsfest aller Zeiten, Teil 1 & Teil 2
programme.desc: Es ist Zims erstes Weihnachtsfest. Als er feststellt, wie fasziniert die Erdlinge vom Weihnachtsmann sind, fasst er einen hinterhältigen Plan: er will selbst in die Rolle des bärtigen alten Mannes schlüpfen.
programme.sub-title: Das schrecklichste Weihnachtsfest aller Zeiten, Teil 1 & Teil 2

programme.title: Regal Academy
programme.desc: Die Freunde müssen sich durch ein mit Fallen durchzogenes Labyrinth kämpfen und ins Schneeschloss gelangen, um die Gefangenen aus den Schneekugeln befreien und zur Regal Academy zurückkehren zu können.

programme.title: Ni Hao, Kai-Lan: Kai-Lans Schnee-Achterbahn
programme.desc: Es hat geschneit und Kai-Lan und ihre Freunde möchten alle zusammen eine Schnee-Achterbahn bauen. Sie bilden kleine Teams und jedes Team übernimmt eine Aufgabe.

programme.title: Robot & Monster: Specknachten
programme.desc: Robot und Monster wollen zusammen mit ihren Familien das Specknachtsfest verbringen. Die Freude ist groß, aber es stellt sich heraus, dass die beiden Familien nichts gemeinsam haben und es kommt zum großen Knall. Sankt Knusprig lenkt ein.

programme.title: Rugrats: Was ist Kwanzaa?
programme.desc: Tante T. stattet Familie Carmichael einen Besuch ab. Gemeinsam wollen sie das afroamerikanische Kwanzaa-Fest feiern.

programme.title: Regal Academy: Weihnachten im Märchenland
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten, und Rose freut sich darüber, dass es den Weihnachtsmann wirklich gibt.

programme.title: Blaze und die Monster-Maschinen: Weihnachten bei den Monster-Maschinen
programme.desc: Blaze hilft dem Weihnachtsmann bei den Vorbereitungen für das große Weihnachtsfest. Doch dann passiert ein kleines Missgeschick, durch das Weihnachten ins Wasser zu fallen droht. Kann Blaze das Fest in letzter Sekunde doch noch retten?!

programme.title: Little Charmers: Santa Sparkle
programme.desc: Als Hazel die Funkelnacht für alle im Zauberstädtchen ruiniert, hoffen die Zaubersternchen, dass Santa Sparkles Magie alles in Ordnung bringt. Doch kommt wahre Funkelnacht-Magie nicht von innen?

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda: Geschenkte Zeit
programme.desc: Zum jährlichen Winterfestival, hat Po nicht genug Geld, um seinem Dad ein Geschenk zu kaufen. Daher nimmt er einen Job als Kopfgeldjäger an und muss einen gefährlichen, entlaufenen Sträfling einfangen. Doch Po’s Plan verläuft nicht wie erhofft.

programme.title: Rocket Power: Nichts für Mädchen / Die Schneekatastrophe
programme.desc: Die Kids gründen ein Rugby-Team, nur Reggie darf nicht mitmachen, weil der Sport nichts für Mädchen sei. / Ein Sturmtief begräbt Ocean Shores unter einer Schneedecke. Ray und Tito sind entsetzt.

programme.title: Clarissa: Weihnachten im Mai
programme.desc: Natürlich ist Clarissa noch zu jung für den Führerschein. Dennoch kreisen ihre Gedanken einzig und allein um einen 1976er Gremlin, den sie in einer Zeitungsanzeige entdeckt hat.

programme.title: Sissi: Die Nacht vor Weihnachten
programme.desc: Weihnachten in Wien ist nicht mehr so schön, wie es einmal war, seit Santa Claus eines seiner Renntiere abhanden gekommen ist. Nach einer Verletzungspause ist es nicht mehr heimgekehrt.

programme.title: Rugrats: Im Spielzeugland, Teil 1
programme.desc: Die Babys besuchen mit ihren Eltern das Feriendorf von Stu. Während sich die Erwachsenen in der Western-Holzhütte einsperren, versucht Angelika Santa Clause seinen Job aufzugeben. Können die Rugrats das angerichtete Chaos wieder in Ordnung bringen?

programme.title: Victorious: Die Weihnachtswichtel
programme.desc: Es weihnachtet an der Schauspielschule, und die Freunde müssen die perfekten Wichtelgeschenke füreinander finden. Denn wer das schlechteste Geschenk hat, muss von Tür zu Tür gehen und mit Sikowitz jodeln.

programme.title: Get Blake!: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!
programme.desc: Die Space-Hörnchen sprühen Roy mit Einschlafspray ein und verschaffen ihm so das verrückteste Date aller Zeiten. // Blake will seine Schuhe kaputtmachen, damit sein Vater ihm Unzerstör-Boots kauft.
programme.sub-title: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!

programme.title: Hey Arnold: Hitzewelle / Der erste Schnee
programme.desc: Die Stadt wird von einer Hitzewelle erfasst und ein Eisverkäufer, der seine Erfrischungen zu Wucherpreisen an den Mann bringt./Der erste Schnee ist gefallen. Arnold kann es kaum erwarten, hinaus zu gehen und mit seinen Freunden Schlitten zu fahren.

programme.title: T.U.F.F. Puppy: Ein verlorenes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Der etwas schusselige, aber liebenswerte Straßenköter Dudley Puppy muss sich um die Verbrechensbekämpfung in seiner Heimatstadt Petropolis kümmern.

programme.title: Rabbids: Invasion
programme.desc: Ein Rabbid will als Weihnachtsmann die Arktis beglücken. / Ein Rabbid will seine Freunde erschrecken. John versucht, Gina mit einem Schnee-Rabbid zu erschrecken. / Als ein Rabbid versehentlich ein Pinguin-Ei zerbricht, will er es ersetzen.
programme.sub-title: Der Weihnachts-Rabbid // Der Schnee-Rabbid // Der einmalige Eier-Rabbid

programme.title: Tesouros de Família
programme.desc: Uma titereira falida volta para casa nas férias e se envolve em uma caça ao tesouro com sua melhor amiga obcecada por paintball, sua avó dançarina de tango e um namorado de infância.

programme.title: A Rainha do Natal
programme.desc: Ashley Mackenzie encontra Ben, um recém-chegado que também ama o feriado. Vendo-o como rival no início, ela percebe que juntos podem criar um Natal ainda mais especial, unindo forças e celebrando o verdadeiro espírito natalino.

programme.title: Romance De Natal Arranjado
programme.desc: A Mandy descobre uma copia velha de "Um Conto de Natal" de Charles Dickens e uma carta de 70 anos para Papai Noel junto com uma moeda de muito valor.

programme.title: O Esquadrão do Papai Noel
programme.desc: Allie, uma professora de arte desempregada, aceita um trabalho no Esquadrão do Papai Noel para ajudar um viúvo rico e suas filhas a redescobrirem a magia do Natal. Enquanto tenta animar o espírito natalino, Allie é recompensada com o amor.

programme.title: Um Conto De Fadas Nas Montanhas
programme.desc: A pediatra Tasha Mason está focada em manter as crianças de sua enfermaria o mais saudáveis possível. Mas quando o belo Príncipe Alexander Cavalieri quebra a perna em uma pista de esqui, Tasha é forçada a cuidar de um mimado membro da realeza.

programme.title: Anjo de Natal
programme.desc: Ashley se sente sozinha no Natal enquanto procura um emprego. Seu vizinho Nick lhe oferece um emprego de assistente no melhor trabalho: ajudar os outros. Há uma coisa que ela não pode contar a ninguém que seu novo chefe é uma espécie de Papai Noel secreto

programme.title: Uma Canção de Natal
programme.desc: Charlotte é nova na cidade e acontece que sua mãe tornou-se íntima do pai de quem parece que ela se tornará sua pior inimiga.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: A Viagem de Joy
programme.desc: O desejo de Natal de uma estudante tímida de liceu torna-se realidade, só que não é exatamente tão maravilhoso como ela esperava.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Unendliche Wälder, eine herbe, unversehrte Natur und launisches Wetter prägen den Naturpark Waadtländer Jura. Wer einmal dort war, weiß um seinen besonderen Reiz: den der Abgeschiedenheit. Mit seinen Seen, Wäldern und von Trockenmauern geprägten Weiden steht das Naturjuwel für das ewige Zusammenspiel von Mensch und Natur. Das Grenzgebiet zu Frankreich bedeckt der riesige Risoud-Wald.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Kaum eine andere Region der Schweiz kann mit so einer Artenvielfalt aufwarten wie die Jungfrau-Region. Die Landschaft um Eiger, Mönch und Jungfrau ist geprägt von krassen Gegensätzen. Extrem trocken ist es auf der Walliser, sehr wasserreich hingegen auf der Seite des Berner Oberlandes.

programme.desc: Das Aufeinandertreffen verschiedener Meeresströmungen führt zu hohem Wellengang. Die Gewässer um Kap Agulhas gelten deswegen, wegen der Riffe und auch wegen seiner Bewohner als sehr gefährlich.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Inmitten von himmlisch schönen Bergeshöhen thront der Piz Beverin über dem Naturpark, dem er seinen Namen verleiht. Zu seinen Füßen erstreckt sich eine Landschaft voller wilder Natur. programme.title: Tasmanien
programme.desc: Tasmanien ist ein einzigartiges Naturparadies: Wilde Strände, dichter Regenwald, zerklüftete Bergketten und alpine Moorlandschaften vereinen sich auf engstem Raum. Auf der Insel leben Wombats, Schnabeligel und Tasmanische Teufel. Die Rangerin Lalani Hyatt patrouilliert täglich durch das Arthur-Pieman-Schutzgebiet, bekämpft Waldbrände, stellt Umweltsünder oder rettet verwaiste Jungtiere.

programme.title: Indien Summer am Polarkreis
programme.desc: Der Herrgott, so ein Sprichwort in der Region, hat ihn nach der Schöpfung einfach vergessen: den Wald im Muddus Nationalpark in Schweden. Ein Urwald - die eine Hälfte voller Bäume, die andere voller Sümpfe und Seen, in dem die älteste Kiefer Schwedens steht. Wenn der Herbst die Bäume und Moose in goldgelbe und tiefrote Farbe taucht, spricht man auch hier im hohen Norden vom Indian Summer.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Burundi
programme.desc: Désiré Nininahazwe, Familienvater und Gründer eines Start ups, kam zum ersten Mal mit dem Trommeln in Kontakt, als er ins SOS-Kinderdorf nach Bujumbura kam, nachdem er seine Eltern im Bürgerkrieg verloren hatte.

programme.title: Madagaskar
programme.sub-title: Die junge Generation im Spannungsfeld des Klimawandels
programme.desc: Während man im westlichen Ausland an Vanilleplantagen und Tropenwälder denkt, spricht man in Madagaskar nur noch von Kéré, der schlimmsten Dürre seit 40 Jahren. Hoffnung gibt, dass sich die SOS-Kinderdörfer um die Kinder des Dorfes kümmern.

programme.title: Sri Lanka
programme.desc: Der fast 30 Jahre währende Bürgerkrieg im Süden Sri Lankas hat das Land verändert. Hunderte Kinder und Waisen standen auf der Straße. Dank der SOS-Kinderdörfer weltweit konnten die meisten in den sechs Kinderdörfern versorgt werden.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Kenia
programme.desc: Asha und Stephen sind im SOS-Kinderdorf in Nairobi aufgewachsen und haben das Beste daraus gemacht. Sie sind "The next Generation". Die Generation, die es schaffen will und auch schaffen wird.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Pelota, die baskische Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Kaum eine Sportart verbindet die Menschen im Baskenland so sehr wie Pelota. Die Region im Grenzgebiet von Frankreich und Spanien, sieht sich als eigenständige Provinz mit einer gemeinsamen Kultur, Sprache und Identität. Das Pelota-Spiel, bei dem ein Ball per Hand oder Schläger gegen eine Hauswand geworfen wird, ist wichtiger Teil davon.

programme.title: Walter Trout, Johnny Griparic, Teddy Andreadis "Zig Zag" & Michael Leasure
programme.desc: Every year since 1970, the German city of Burghausen has been hosting one of the largest jazz festivals in the world. During Burghausen International Jazz Week, Burghausen becomes a 'Bavarian jazz mecca': guests from all over the world join the Burghausers to enjoy the most wonderful jazz performances as the colorful hustle and bustle of spectators and musicians shake up the city. One of the bands performing here in 2019 is the Walter Trout Band. Trout, who was born in New Jersey and is based in Los Angeles, is a world-famous contemporary blues rock guitarist and vocalist.

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: Eliane Elias
programme.desc: There's no question about it: with a Grammy for Best Latin Jazz Album for her recording ‘Made In Brazil', seven previous Grammy nominations, four ‘Gold Disc Awards', and three ‘Best Vocal Album Awards' in Japan, Eliane Elias has taken her place in the pantheon of music giants. In her projects, Elias wears many hats: she serves as producer, composer, lyricist, arranger, pianist, and vocalist. In this concert broadcast, recorded live at the Philharmonie in Munich, Elias shows her distinctive and immediately recognizable musical style, which blends her Brazilian samba roots and her sensuous, alluring voice with her impressive instrumental bebop, jazz, classical, and compositional skills. She is an artist beyond category, and in this concert she performs with Jay Randall Anderson (bass) and Adam Nussbaum (drums).

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Thelonious Monk, Charlie Rouse, Ben Riley & Larry Gales
programme.desc: The idiosyncratic pianist and composer Thelonious Monk (1917-1982) is one of the all-time greats of jazz. His music went largely misunderstood for the first 15 years of his career, after which he was rightly hailed as a genius, and received credit as a founding father of bebop. Several concerts from his 1966 European tour were recorded for television, featuring his quartet of Charles Rouse (tenor saxophone), Lawrence Gales (bass) and Benjamin Riley (drums). His quartet performed Epistrophy, 'Round Midnight, and Lulu's Back in Town in Warsaw for Polish television on April 4, 1966. On April 17, the same quartet performed a short set in Copenhagen for Danish television, featuring Lulu's Back in Town, Don't Blame Me, and Epistrophy.

programme.title: Omar Sosa, Childo Tomas, Ernesto Simpson & Leandro Saint-Hill
programme.desc: While always keeping one foot firmly anchored in the traditions of his home country, Cuba, Omar Sosa tirelessly explores music from the Caribbean to India, and West Africa to the Arab world. Since he left Cuba in 1993, the pianist has been blending his Afro-Cuban roots with jazz, hip hop, electro and world music. For his 2018 performance at Théâtre de Villefranche-sur-Saône, he brings to stage his Quarteto Afrocubano members Childo Tomas (electric bass & vocals), Ernesto Simpson (drums), and Leandro Saint-Hill (saxophones, flute, percussion & vocals). Together, they create a riveting instrumental dialogue. Celebrating rhythm in all its forms, this Omar Sosa concert is an intense and mystical experience.

programme.title: Steve Gadd
programme.desc: Many of pianist Chick Corea's compositions have become jazz standards. As a member of Miles Davis' band in the late 1960s, he participated in the birth of the electric jazz fusion movement. In the 1970s, Corea founded the legendary jazz fusion group Return to Forever. Along with Herbie Hancock, McCoy Tyner and Keith Jarrett, Corea is one of the biggest modern jazz pianists. He continued musical collaborations with a diverse range of artists, exploring various musical styles. This broadcast features three performances that illustrate Chick Corea's many talents.

programme.title: Manu Dibango, Daniel Rallo, Jerry Malekani & Frederic Gaillardet
programme.sub-title: Soul Makossa: Manu Dibango in Stuttgart
programme.desc: Manu Dibango, one of Africa's biggest musical stars and top saxophonists, is an indispensable artist. He was one of the first African musicians to score a worldwide hit with his 1972 release “Soul Makossa”, paving the way for many other artists. The very concept of world music owes much to him. A superb stage performer with great communicative humour, Dibango is above all one of the founding fathers of a modern African musical style that is open to jazz, R&B, salsa, gospel, funk, and reggae. This concert showcases all these genres, and features an excellent line-up of musicians from the four corners of the planet.

programme.title: Birth of Invention
programme.desc: By its very name this is multi-instrumentalist characterized by nonconformity, free-form improvisation, sound experiments, musical virtuosity, and satire. Featuring rock, pop, jazz, jazz fusion, orchestral and innovative and stylistically diverse. As well as progressive rock, art rock, and post-progressive. The music was grounded in the rock of the 1960s, especially the acid rock and psychedelic rock movements. With Frank Zappa, Captain Beefhart & King Crimson

programme.title: Various Artists
programme.desc: The best of Qello Concerts

programme.title: Psychedelic Rock
programme.desc: The sound of psychedelic rock involved electronic instruments, guitar effects, oriental instruments, unconventional song structures, lyrics that referenced drugs or fantasy books, with extended instrumental sections. The genre bridged the transition from early blues and folk-based rock to progressive rock and hard rock. This episode features The Moody Blues, Emerson Lake & Palmer and Traffic

programme.title: Jazz Rock
programme.desc: Jazz rock generally grew out of the artistically ambitious rock subgenres of the late 1960s and early 1970s psychedelia, progressive rock, and the singer-songwriter movement. Jazz rock includes extensive improvisation and features soloists with distinctive sounds. This programme explores the music of artists Steely Dan, Doobie Brothers, Boz Scaggs.

programme.title: Progressive Rock
programme.desc: By the dawn of the seventies, progressive rock freed bands of the limitations of four-minute songs, allowing musicians to evolve a single track over a whole side of vinyl, draw on classical sources and create music in more complex, time signatures. Moog Synthesizers were portable and affordable, allowing bands to create orchestral effects. Such devices added a spectrum of new sounds and possibilities for musicians. This new world brought artists such as Rush, Yes & Atomic Rooster into the mainstream.

programme.title: Soft Rock
programme.desc: During the 1960s rock n roll splintered into a rainbow of genres – musicians were experimenting. Soft rock began as a blend of the progressive rock quest for musicianship and the songwriter's love of pop. It originated in the late 1960s in Southern California and the United Kingdom. The style relied on simple, melodic songs with big, lush productions. This new genre established bands such as Supertramp, ELO & Barclay James Harvest

programme.title: Metalheads
programme.desc: Metal combines overdriven guitars with heavy drums, often double bass drums, bass lines working with and against guitar lines and vocals from voices at the limit of their power. In blues, the raw voice might sing over the gentle acoustic guitar or the mellow church organ. In hard rock, the overdriven guitar might howl against the slower groove of bass and drums. In metal, everything is at 10. With Motörhead, Testament and AC/DC

programme.title: British Metal
programme.desc: Music offered an escape from the drudgery of real life, if not a direct route to fame and riches. They came from tough working-class backgrounds. Factory work or steel rolling were starting to vanish. At the same time, British punk was born and spread outwards, its anger and nihilistic world view the antithesis of everything that had gone before. British Heavy Metal exploded. This episode features bands such as Judas Priest, Saxon and Iron Maiden

programme.title: US Punk Rock
programme.desc: A stripped back sound. Fast and loud. Punk played cheap Fender guitars at full volume, so the notes came out distorted by overdrive. This stripped-down amateur sound rejected musical virtuosity in favour of simple chord changes, energy, commitment, anger, and noise. The lyrics are frank, confrontational, and often political. The US stars included The New York Dolls, The Ramones and The Dead Kennedys

programme.title: Post-Punk
programme.desc: Post-punk emerged from the Punk scene. It had the same kind of DIY ethos, a very kind of hands on approach, but was more experimental, more intellectual, and more artistic in its approach to music. It wasn't about being a rock star it was almost the opposite – anti-fashion, anti-ego, in a sense, and these very introspective songs, which tended to dwell on the kind of more maudlin aspects of daily life, and what we all experience.

programme.title: US Heavy Metal
programme.desc: The US heavy metal sound has big hooks, melodic choruses, and monster ballads with nearly every song featuring one guitar solo. Vocals are melodic, and high-pitched. They also include extensive use of harmonies, particularly in the ballads – slow, emotional songs that gradually build to a strong finale. Lyrics tended to deal with love and lust. With Motley Crue, Poison & Ratt.

programme.title: Glam Rock
programme.desc: Self-glorifying and decadent, glam rock positioned itself as a backlash against the rock mainstream of the late 1960s on the periphery of society and rock culture, glam rockers were, rebelling against the rebellion. At Glam's core musically was a heavy guitar sound shaped by hard rock. With T-Rex, Mott the Hoople & The Sweet

programme.title: Women Who Rock
programme.desc: In the '60s, artists such as Grace Slick and Janis Joplin, were fronting A-list bands. Garage rock, all girl bands sprang up across the US in the 1960s and were playing rock 'n' roll on their own terms whilst breaking new ground. As rock developed in the late 1960s and 1970s alongside the women's liberation movement, women refused to be just the pretty singer fronting a group. This episode features bands such as Heart, Suzie Quatro and The Bangles.

programme.title: Pop Rock
programme.desc: New Wave and post-punk were the successors of the raw nihilism of punk. New Wave was brighter, more pop, synth-heavy and very dance-able. The Pop Rock sound of the 1970s & 1980s was a tune heavy blend of punk minimalism, art rock synthesizer and pop melodies. Bands like The Cars, Go-Go's and Huey Lewis & the News embraced the blend of new wave and pop.

programme.title: Leonardo García Alarcón, Cappella Mediterranea & Mariana Flores
programme.sub-title: Vocal baroque works by Cavalli, Strozzi & Bembo
programme.desc: Argentinian conductor and harpsichordist Leonardo García Alarcón leads his ensemble Cappella Mediterranea in a program of Italian Baroque music. The ensemble performs some of the finest Baroque pieces composed by Francesco Cavalli, a prominent composer in 17th-century Venice, and two of his famous students, Barbara Strozzi and Antonia Bembo. Argentinian soprano Mariana Flores presents the vocal works. On the program are ‘Mira questi due lumi' from Cavalli's Le nozze di Teti e di Peleo, ‘Dimmi, Amor, che farò' from L'Oristeo, ‘Sinfonia della notte' from L'Egisto, and ‘E vuol dunque Ciprigna' from Ercole Amante ‘M'ingannasti in verità' from Bembo's Produzioni armoniche consacrate a Luigi XIV Strozzi's Sino alla morte, Che si può fare, Lagrime mie, L'amante segreto, and è Pazzo il moi core Biagio Marini's La Romanesca Tarquinio Merula's Aria Sopra La Cieccona and Dario Castello's Sonata Seconda. This performance was recorded at the magnificent Église Notre-Dame of Sablé-sur-Sarthe, France, on August 26, 2020.

programme.title: Les Arts Florissants & Paul Agnew
programme.desc: Italian composer Claudio Monteverdi (1567-1643) composed nine books of madrigals in half a century, which helped transform the genre from the polyphonic, a cappella madrigals of the late Renaissance to the ‘concertato' madrigals of the early Baroque, shifting the style's focus to the ability of music to express emotions contained in a text. In 2011, British tenor Paul Agnew and renowned Baroque ensemble Les Arts Florissants started recording eight books of Monteverdi's madrigals. In this program, Agnew leads Les Arts Florissants in the madrigals of Book I. Published on New Year's day of 1587, Book I consist of seventeen madrigals for five voices. This performance was recorded at the Cité de la musique in Paris, France, in 2011.

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shai & Arielle Beck
programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration - I
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shaï, and Arielle Beck violinists Gidon Kremer, Maxim Vengerov, and Tedi Papavrami cellist Mischa Maisky, Flugelhorn player Sergei Nakariakov, as well as her daughter and grandson: Lyda Chen-Argerich (piano and viola) and David Chen-Argerich (piano). On the program are Alfred Schnittke's Congratulatory rondo for piano and violin Preludes No. 5, 21, and 24 from Mieczysław Weinberg's 24 Preludes, Op. 100 (arranged for solo violin by G. Kremer) ‘Waltz' and ‘Slava' from Sergei Rachmaninoff's 6 Morceaux, Op. 11, and Romance for six hands Fritz Kreisler's Liebesleid Robert Schumann's Fantasiestücke Op. 73, and Piano Quintet in E-flat major, Op. 44 and ‘Laideronnette, impératrice des Pagodes' from Maurice Ravel's Ma mère l'Oye. This performance was recorded on June 11, 2021.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Klaus Tönshoff, Danish National Symphony Orchestra & DR Big Band
programme.desc: Musicians of the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, the DR Big Band, and the Danish National Vocal Ensemble join forces under the baton of Klaus Tönshoff in this dazzling concert featuring great songs from black and white cinema. Norwegian mezzosoprano Tuva Semmingsen sings ‘Diamonds Are A Girl's Best Friend', from Gentlemen Prefer Blondes, ‘My Favorite Things' from The Sound of Music, ‘Over the Rainbow' from The Wizard of Oz, ‘Moon River' from Breakfast at Tiffany's, and many other unforgettable hits. This concert performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2020.

programme.title: Maria Luigia Borsi & Antonio Artese
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Puccini, Leoncavallo a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Maria Luigia Borsi (soprano) and Antonio Artese (piano) present a recital consisting of several songs and arias. On the program are Francesco Paolo Tosti's Sogno, ‘A vucchella, and L'alba separa dalla luce l'ombra Giacomo Puccini's Sole e amore, Sogno d'or, “Donde lieta” (from La Bohème), “Il bel sogno di Doretta” (from La rondine), and “O mio babbino caro” (from Gianni Schicchi) Renato Brogi's Presentimento, Ruggero Leoncavallo's Mattinata, and Alfredo Catalini's Chanson Groenlandaise.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.

programme.desc: Tasmanien ist ein einzigartiges Naturparadies: Wilde Strände, dichter Regenwald, zerklüftete Bergketten und alpine Moorlandschaften vereinen sich auf engstem Raum. Auf der Insel leben Wombats, Schnabeligel und Tasmanische Teufel. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod

Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: El Rey y su hermana, la Princesa Cristina, comparten sus recuerdos de infancia en el palacio. "En realidad no era un entorno agradable para vivir, más bien parecía un hotel", recuerda el Rey al describir las habitaciones donde él y sus hermanas crecieron en el ala sur del palacio. La Princesa Heredera Victoria nos muestra objetos de valor incalculable en sus habitaciones favoritas "Es un patrimonio cultural fantástico y es impresionante que se conserven estos ambientes, teniendo en cuenta lo antiguos que son. Es un tesoro extraordinario y accesible que nos pertenece a todos", afirma. Los espectadores también tienen la oportunidad de adentrarse entre bastidores antes de una visita de Estado, escuchar historias de fantasmas reales, así como a historiadores, expertos y artesanos que nos ofrecen un retrato único de un tesoro nacional: nuestro Palacio Real.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: Nos subimos a un andamio para averiguar más cosas sobre la renovación de la fachada y llegar al fondo de la cuestión de si el viejo castillo está embrujado. Síganos por los salones dorados y las oscuras bóvedas de los sótanos. El Palacio Real de Estocolmo tiene más de mil habitaciones y cientos de años de historia real. El Rey y su hermana, la princesa Cristina, nos cuentan cómo fue crecer en el palacio. La Princesa Victoria muestra objetos de valor incalculable.

programme.desc: Con l'evoluzione della guerra, molte tecniche e tecnologie militari sono state adattate per l'uso in ambiente urbano dalle unità di polizia di tutto il mondo. Questo episodio offre agli spettatori una prospettiva intima su come ci si sente a "entrare nella testa" di personale speciale di polizia e su come l'uso di strategie ed equipaggiamenti di tipo militare permetta loro di salvare vite umane. Dal controllo delle rivolte in Sudafrica e le lezioni apprese dai suoi eccessi, alla creazione da parte del capo della polizia di Los Angeles Robert Gates di una squadra d'élite S.W.A.T., CQB mostrerà come, negli ultimi 30 anni, la lotta contro la criminalità urbana si sia evoluta in uno scenario militare, con entrambe le parti che utilizzano armi e tattiche sempre più complesse.

programme.title: [창덕궁 봄꽃 개화 현장] 봄꽃의 향연, 창덕궁 나들이
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널창덕궁은 태종 때 건립된 조선왕조의 왕궁으로, 처음에는 경복궁의 이궁으로 지어졌지만 경복궁보다 더욱 오래 법궁의 역할을 해왔습니다. 특히 창덕궁 후원은 한국의 유일한 궁궐후원이라는 점에서 그 가치가 매우 높지요. 한국의 대표적인 정원인 창덕궁이 봄을 맞이하는 아름다운 모습을 감상해보세요! ※ 창덕궁 (사적 제122호, 1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [오늘도 평화로운 갯벌] 해질녘의 광활한 갯벌, 순천만
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널순천만은 남해안 중서부에 위치한 만으로, 갯벌에 펼쳐지는 갈대밭과 칠면초 군락 등이 어우러져 아름다운 해안 생태경관을 보입니다. 넓은 갯벌에는 다양한 갯벌 생물들이 살고, 천연기념물인 흑두루미를 비롯한 국제 희귀 조류가 찾는 순천만의 풍경을 감상해 보세요! ※ 전라남도 순천시 순천만 (명승 제41호) / 한국의 갯벌 (2021년 유네스코 세계자연유산)

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.2
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.4
programme.desc: 주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 그을음으로 먹을 만들다. 먹장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널먹은 예로부터 선비의 친구 문방사우(먹, 종이, 붓, 벼루) 중 하나로 우리의 뛰어난 기록문화유산들을 만드는 중요한 소재였습니다. 전통방식으로 만들어 지는 먹은 기름은 태워서 그을음으로 만드는 유연먹과 소나무 그을음으로 만드는 송연먹이 있습니다. '한상묵 장인'이 전통 먹가마를 이용하여 송연먹을 제작하는 과정을 함께 감상해봅시다. (한상묵 / 전통 먹장 숙련기술자)

programme.title: 칼끝에서 피어나는 장인정신. 소반장
programme.desc: 반(小盤)이란 음식을 담은 그릇을 올려 놓는 작은 상으로, 한국의 식생활에서 부터 제사의례에 이르기까지 여러 용도로 쓰이며, 이것을 만드는 기술 또는 그 장인(匠人)을 소반장이라 합니다. 작지만 부족함이 없으며 실용성과 멋을 두루 갖춘 우리 전통의 소리를 ASMR 풀버젼으로 감상해보시죠. (이종덕 / 국가무형문화재 소반장 전승교육사)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 정성을 빚다. 떡 만들기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널명절 때마다 함께 나누어 먹는 음식 떡. 밤, 대추, 잣, 팥고물과 함께 쪄낸 떡 초두점증병과 쑥과 함께 만든 경단인 쑥구리단자가 만들어지는 모습을 보며 문화유산이 정성스럽게 만들어지는 모습을 함께 공감해 보아요. (정길자 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 보유자)

programme.title: 기품있는 한옥의 멋. 고택의 하루
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널해 뜨기 전 너른 마당을 빗자루로 쓰는 소리, 어머니의 밥 짓는 정지의 풍경, 타닥타닥 장작개비가 타들어 가는 아궁이의 소리 등 지친 일상 속에서 하루쯤 푸근하게 쉬어가고 싶은 550년 역사를 자랑하는 오래된 고택에서 다양한 일상의 풍경을 이른 아침부터 밤까지 생생하게 들려드립니다. ※ 안동 진성이씨 온혜파 종택 (국가민속문화재 제295호)

programme.title: 사방탁자를 만들다. 소목장
programme.desc: 소목장은 건물의 창호, 목기, 목가구를 제작하는 목수를 말합니다. 이들은 전통 목공예기법으로 무늬가 있는 나무를 사용하여 자연스러운 미를 살려냅니다. 검소한 조선시대 문방생활을 운치있게 만들어주던 사방탁자를 만드는 과정을 감상해 보세요. (박명배 / 국가무형문화재 소목장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 천년을 견디는 한지의 비밀. 닥나무 껍질 벗기기
programme.desc: 전통 한지는 천 년을 견디며 변하지 않는 뛰어난 가치를 지니고 있습니다. 99번의 손길을 거쳐 100번째 탄생하는 땀과 정신의 결정체인 전통 한지의 제작 과정 중 주원료가 되는 닥나무의 껍질을 벗기는 과정을 함께 감상해보시죠. (김춘호 / 경북무형문화재 문경 한지장 전승교육사)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 병풍을 만들다, 배첩장
programme.desc: 배첩은 글씨나 그림의 보존성과 아름다움을 높이기 위한 전통 서화 처리기법을 말합니다. 액자를 만들거나 병풍, 족자, 책을 엮는 등의 작업을 주로 하는데, 장인의 솜씨가 그 퀄리티를 좌우하죠. 배첩장이 10폭 병풍을 만드는 과정을 함께 감상해보시죠. (홍종진 / 충북무형문화재 배첩장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 소리의 맥을 잇다, 대금장
